cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this lab or its methodology, please cite it as below."
title: "multi-agent-fiction-lab: A PM-driven lab for multi-agent collaborative fiction writing"
abstract: >-
  multi-agent-fiction-lab is a working methodology for AI-augmented
  collaborative long-form fiction writing, designed from a Product Manager
  perspective. It documents the architecture of two cooperating agent teams
  (a 4-agent outline-discussion team and a 5-agent prose-review team), a
  memory-as-workflow design pattern (curated input packages rather than
  vector retrieval), and case studies of novel-length fiction produced
  through this workflow. The lab is structured to serve three audiences
  simultaneously — hiring managers (60s), multi-agent practitioners (10min),
  and academic researchers (40min) — via a layered docs / examples / research
  architecture.
